<sect1 id="s1-rpm-specref-">
<title>Comments</title>
<indexterm>
<primary>spec file!comments in</primary>
<secondary></secondary>
<tertiary></tertiary>
<see></see>
</indexterm>

Comments are a way to make RPM ignore a line in the spec file.  To create a
comment, enter an octothorp (<tt?>#</tt?>) at the start of the line.  Any
text following the comment character will be ignored by RPM:

<figure id="sc-rpm-specref-">
<title>*** Enter New Title Here ***</title>
<screen width="60">
# This is the spec file for playmidi 2.3...
</screen>
</figure>
Comments can be placed in any section of the spec file.

See also: Section <xref linkend="inside-comments">.

<indexterm>
<primary>spec file!comments in|)</primary>
<secondary></secondary>
<tertiary></tertiary>
<see></see>
</indexterm>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="s1-rpm-specref-">
<title>The Preamble</title>
<sect2 id="s2-rpm-specref-">
<title>Package Naming Tags</title>
<sect3 id="s3-rpm-specref-">
<title>The <tt?>name</tt?> Tag</title>
<indexterm>
