<sect2 id="s2-rpm-specref-">
<title>Install-/Erase-time Scripts</title>
These scripts are executed whenever the package is installed or erased.
Each script can consist of any valid <tt?>sh</tt?> commands.

Note: Each of the following scripts can be made specific to a particular
subpackage by adding the subpackage name, and optionally, the <tt?>-n</tt?>
option:

<figure id="sc-rpm-specref-">
<title>*** Enter New Title Here ***</title>
<screen width="60">
%post bar

%preun -n bar
</screen>
</figure>
The subpackage name and usage of the <tt?>-n</tt?> option must match those
defined with the <tt?>%package</tt?> directive.

Each script has the following environment variable defined:

<itemizedlist mark="bullet">
<listitem>
<para>
<tt?>RPM_INSTALL_PREFIX</tt?>

</para>
</listitem>

</itemizedlist>
For more information on this environment variable please see section
<xref linkend="inside-install/erase"> on page <xref linkend="inside-install/erase">.

